---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import marcusAurelius from "../../assets/marcus-aurelius.webp";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Stoic Wisdom for Modern Life | Success Odyssey Hub"
  description="Learn how ancient Stoic philosophy can help you build resilience, find inner peace, and maintain clarity in our fast-paced modern world."
  keywords="stoicism, philosophy, resilience, inner peace, mental strength, Marcus Aurelius, Seneca, stoic principles, dichotomy of control"
  image={marcusAurelius}
  type="article"
  datePublished="2025-01-12T00:00:00Z"
  dateModified="2025-01-12T00:00:00Z"
  author="Success Odyssey Hub"
>
  <article class="blog-page" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/BlogPosting">
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1 itemprop="headline">Stoic Wisdom for Modern Life</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <time datetime="2025-01-12" itemprop="datePublished">January 12, 2025</time>
        <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2025-01-12T00:00:00Z" />
        <span class="reading-time" itemprop="timeRequired" content="PT6M">6 min read</span>
        <div class="tags">
          <span class="tag" itemprop="keywords">Stoicism</span>
          <span class="tag" itemprop="keywords">Philosophy</span>
          <span class="tag" itemprop="keywords">Resilience</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Optimized hero image with Astro Image component -->
    <figure itemprop="image" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject">
      <Image
        src={marcusAurelius}
        alt="Ancient Stoic philosophy symbolized by a serene marble column against a blue sky, representing wisdom, resilience and inner peace"
        class="hero-image"
        width={900}
        height={200}
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
        format="webp"
        quality={85}
      />
      <meta itemprop="url" content={new URL(marcusAurelius.src, Astro.site).toString()} />
      <meta itemprop="width" content="900" />
      <meta itemprop="height" content="200" />
    </figure>

    <div class="content" itemprop="articleBody">
      <p class="lead">
        In a world of constant change and uncertainty, ancient Stoic philosophy offers timeless wisdom for navigating life's challenges with grace, resilience, and inner peace.
      </p>

      <h2>The Foundation of Stoicism</h2>
      <p>
        Stoicism teaches us to focus on what we can control and accept what we cannot. This fundamental principle, when truly understood and applied, becomes a powerful tool for reducing anxiety, improving decision-making, and finding contentment regardless of external circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Stoic Principles</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>The Dichotomy of Control:</strong> Understanding the difference between what is "up to us" and what is "not up to us" is the cornerstone of Stoic thinking. Our thoughts, judgments, desires, and actions are within our control—everything else is not.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Virtue as the Highest Good:</strong> The Stoics believed that virtue—wisdom, justice, courage, and temperance—is the only true good. External things like wealth, fame, or even health are "indifferent" when it comes to living a good life.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Present Moment Awareness:</strong> Marcus Aurelius reminds us that "the present moment is the only time over which we have dominion." By focusing on the here and now, we can respond thoughtfully rather than react emotionally.
      </p>

      <h2>Practical Applications</h2>
      <p>
        Start each day by reminding yourself of what you can and cannot control. When faced with challenges, ask: "Is this within my power to change?" If yes, take action. If no, practice acceptance and focus your energy elsewhere.
      </p>

      <p>
        Practice negative visualization—imagining loss or setbacks—not to invite negativity, but to appreciate what you have and build resilience for when difficulties arise.
      </p>

      <blockquote itemprop="citation">
        "You have power over your mind—not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength." - Marcus Aurelius
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Stoicism isn't about suppressing emotions or becoming indifferent to life. It's about developing the wisdom to respond rather than react, finding peace in any circumstance, and building unshakeable inner strength.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Author Info with proper Schema.org markup -->
    <div class="author-info" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization">
      <svg width="60" height="60" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="border-radius: 50%; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); padding: 12px;">
        <path d="M12 2L13.09 8.26L20 9L13.09 9.74L12 16L10.91 9.74L4 9L10.91 8.26L12 2Z" fill="white"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="author-details">
        <h4 itemprop="name">Success Odyssey Hub</h4>
        <meta itemprop="url" content={Astro.site?.toString()} />
        <p>We explore ancient wisdom and modern applications for building resilience and living a meaningful life.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Related Articles with proper semantic markup -->
    <nav class="related-articles" aria-label="Related articles">
      <h3>Related Articles</h3>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/blog/success-philosophy" rel="related">
          <span>The Philosophy of Success</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/mental-models" rel="related">
          <span>Mental Models for Better Decision Making</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/vision-to-reality" rel="related">
          <span>From Vision to Reality: The Art of Execution</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Breadcrumb for better navigation -->
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" style="margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e7eb);">
      <ol itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList" style="display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; list-style: none; padding: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
          <a itemprop="item" href="/">
            <span itemprop="name">Home</span>
          </a>
          <meta itemprop="position" content="1" />
          <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem;">/</span>
        </li>
        <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
          <a itemprop="item" href="/blog">
            <span itemprop="name">Blog</span>
          </a>
          <meta itemprop="position" content="2" />
          <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem;">/</span>
        </li>
        <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
          <span itemprop="name">Stoic Wisdom for Modern Life</span>
          <meta itemprop="position" content="3" />
        </li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
  </article>

  <style>
    /* Hero image - Works with Astro Image component */
    :global(.hero-image) {
      width: 100%;
      height: 200px !important;
      object-fit: cover;
      border-radius: 8px;
      display: block;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    figure {
      margin: 2rem 0;
      padding: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      :global(.hero-image) {
        height: 150px !important;
      }
    }

    /* Article structure */
    .blog-page {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .article-header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .article-header h1 {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary, #3b82f6), var(--color-accent, #f59e0b));
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
      line-height: 1.2;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .article-meta {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary, #666);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .article-meta time {
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary, #666);
    }

    .reading-time {
      color: var(--color-primary, #3b82f6);
    }

    .tags {
      display: flex;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .tag {
      background: var(--color-bg-tertiary, #f9fafb);
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
      padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
      border-radius: 1rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    /* Content styling */
    .content {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--color-primary, #3b82f6);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .content h2 {
      color: var(--color-primary, #3b82f6);
      margin-top: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .content p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
    }

    .content strong {
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    blockquote {
      border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary, #3b82f6);
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 2rem 0;
      background: var(--color-accent-light, #f8fafc);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
    }

    /* Author info */
    .author-info {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: var(--color-accent-light, #f8fafc);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .author-details {
      flex: 1;
    }

    .author-details h4 {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .author-details p {
      color: var(--color-text-secondary, #666);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    /* Related articles */
    .related-articles {
      margin-top: 3rem;
      padding-top: 2rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e7eb);
    }

    .related-articles h3 {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
    }

    .related-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .related-grid a {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      background: var(--color-accent-light, #f8fafc);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border, #e5e7eb);
      border-radius: 8px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--color-text-primary, #1a1a1a);
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .related-grid a:hover {
      background: var(--color-bg-tertiary, #f3f4f6);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    /* Mobile responsive */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .blog-page {
        padding: 1rem;
      }

      .article-meta {
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
      }

      .content {
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .lead {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
      }

      .content h2 {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
      }

      .content p {
        font-size: 1rem;
      }

      .author-info {
        padding: 1.5rem;
      }

      .related-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>